Makes more sense now <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Oxoxo:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> What Rom means by controlling aggro is that sometimes you dont need to cast concussion. You can just wait, and depending on who is tanking, distance and how many people on the raid are all factors in your ability to control your own aggro as well. You dont have to chain concussion as much as you think you do. Good wizards through lots of experience learn the spell sets, positioning, tanks, raid force they are using on how to maximize DPS for a given encounter. It is not as simple as &quot;chaining concussion&quot; Sure you can do that but if thats your only formula your DPS prolly sucks on raid mobs <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Except that we weren't really talking about concussion, we were talking about spellcasting subtlety.  My point sort of assumed that what you said was true..  Assuming that you don't simply chaincast concussion, and you're really &quot;good&quot; at managing your aggro, Spellcasting Subtlety will increase the amount of damage you will be able to do.  You'll be able to spend less time in between casts.  There are only a few situations where I can see SCS <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>not</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> being useful, and one of those was a situation where you would be forced to cast fewer concussions than you would have otherwise been able to.  <br>
<br>
IE say your nuke strat is DoR, DoR, Concuss, DoR, DoR, Concuss, DoR, DoR, Concuss-- all chaincasted with no extra downtime..  In order to increase your dps you'd have to drop out a concussion, and the 20% protection from SCS might not make up for it.  From Rombus's last comment it seems that this is actually the case for him.  <br>
<br>
However, if your normal nuke pattern includes time not spent casting spells, spellcasting subtlety should let you increase your damage without losing any of the aggro saved from concussion. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=25369.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=25369.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=25369.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=25369.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a> <b>5</b> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=25369.topic&start=101&stop=106>6</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=25369.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=25369.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25369.topic&index=100><img src=http://www.graffe.com/images/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=25369.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.threadControl?topicID=25369.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub14